commit 333e790d1de8a60d387208ca89db88bb2c54fa18
Author: webimpress <contact@webimpress.com>
Date:   Wed Dec 12 23:46:39 2018 +0000

    Fix for PSR2 ClassDeclarationSniff - position of class name
    
    Follow up #2300
    As the previous hotfix was merged and unmerged this hotfix provides
    better check for class names after implements/extends keywords in
    class/interface/trait definition.
    
    According to PSR-2 multiline definition is allowed only if we implements
    more than one interface (or interface extends more than one interface).
    Everything else should be always in the same line as class name.

