commit cb4f965c69e0d7357cfe040d482a48d9c93a9013
Author: jrfnl <jrfnl@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed Jan 2 09:43:28 2019 +0100

    Travis: add additional validation for the PEAR package.xml file
    
    This PR adds a custom script which will validate the `<contents>` and `<phprelease>`  tags in the PEAR-targeted `package.xml` file.
    
    The script executes the following check to verify the validity of the tags:
    * Check that every file mentioned in the `<contents>` tag exists.
    * Check that the value of the `role` attribute for a `<file>` tag is valid.
    * Check that the value of the `baseinstalldir` attribute for a `<file>` tag is valid.
    * Checks that all files in the `src` and `tests` directories are listed in the `<contents>` tag.
    * Check that every file mentioned in the `<phprelease>` tags exists.
    * Check that the value of the `as` attribute for a `<install>` tag is valid.
    * Checks that all files in the `tests` directory are listed in the `<phprelease>` tags.
    
    More/improved checks can be added if/when needed, but this should prevent the most common issues.
    
    This check only needs to be run on one build as the results won't change between PHP versions.
    For that reason, I've elected to add it to one of the `CUSTOM_INI` runs to balance out the runs some more.
    
    As the PHP version makes no difference to the `xmllint` check, I've moved that to a lower PHP version, so we can use a higher (faster) PHP version for this additional check.

commit 4fe41bbdeda9b0918886433cdc054487fc389753
Author: jrfnl <jrfnl@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed Jan 2 09:28:59 2019 +0100

    Hotfix for PEAR install
    
    In the WordPressCS  repo we received a bug report from someone using PHPCS 3.4.0 but missing the `Generic.WhiteSpace.LanguageConstructSpacing` sniff.
    
    Turned out that that sniff is missing from the `package.xml` file which is why it's not available when someone is using a PEAR install of PHPCS.
    
    I've now done a comprehensive check of all relevant files in the repo versus the files listed in the `<contents>` tag of the `package.xml` file and found some more discrepancies with this commit as a result.
    
    As this basically means that the PEAR install is currently "broken" with regards to the `Code` report (PHPCS 3.0), the `Generic.Formatting.SpaceBeforeCast` sniff (PHPCS 3.4.0) as well as the `Generic.WhiteSpace.LanguageConstructSpacing` sniff (PHPCS 3.3.0), this should be considered a hotfix.

