commit 88aeb679764f89b9ac79c1b6cf242916b697e419
Author: jrfnl <jrfnl@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed Nov 28 03:40:02 2018 +0100

    Squiz/PostStatementComment: fix fixer conflict
    
    [Fixer conflicts series PR]
    
    When a JS file contains a `//` comment on the very first line of the file, the fixer unnecessarily added a new line before it, which would cause a fixer conflict with the `Squiz.WhiteSpace.SuperfluousWhitespace` sniff.
    
    The fixer conflict can be reproduced by checking out just the new `PostStatementCommentUnitTest.2.js` test case file from this PR and running the sniff - as it is currently in `master` - over it using the `Squiz` standard.
    
    `phpcbf -s ./Squiz/Tests/Commenting/PostStatementCommentUnitTest.2.js --standard=Squiz -vv`
    
    This commit fixes the fixer conflict and adds a new unit test file guarding against it.
    
    Additional notes:
    * Added minor defensive coding improvements.
    * Added tests confirming the correct handling of post statement comments for PHP closures.
    * Added tests confirming the correct handling of the new PHPCS annotations.
    * Removed some redundant break statements from the unit test file.

