commit 395ecbd0056547a80f6c6d7fafda36bbd814b645
Author: jrfnl <jrfnl@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon Dec 3 06:52:16 2018 +0100

    Squiz/ControlSignature: fix fixer conflict
    
    [Fixer conflict series PR]
    
    The check to prevent the sniff from kicking in during live coding/at the end of a file wasn't stable enough and allowed the sniff to kick in anyway if there was a new line or comment after the control structure keyword.
    This, in turn, would cause a fixer conflict with `EndFileNewLine` sniffs and - depending on the control structure - other sniffs.
    
    The fixer conflict can be reproduced using this code sample:
    ```php
    <?php
    foreach
    
    ```
    and this command:
    `phpcbf ./testfile.php --standard=Squiz
    
    And while PSR2 does not generate a fixer conflict for this code sample, incorrect fixes would still be made resulting in (more) parse errors.
    Using this code sample:
    ```php
    <?php
    for
    
    ```
    
    Using the following command:
    `phpcbf ./testfile.php --standard=PSR2`
    
    This would be fixed to:
    ```php
    for {
        ;
    }
    ```
    
    While rare to come across this in practice, the sniff should be stable and prevent this situation from ever occurring.
    By changing the 'live coding' check to look at more than just the next token, this issue is prevented.
    
    Includes unit test demonstrating the issue.

commit 3630370d275f82be40627860f6f11446290f6a0b
Author: jrfnl <jrfnl@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon Dec 3 05:16:49 2018 +0100

    Generic/InlineControlStructure: fix fixer conflict / parse error resilience
    
    The `Generic.ControlStructures.InlineControlStructure` sniff did not handle live coding situations/parse errors and would try to fix the file anyway.
    
    This causes a fixer conflict. This is now fixed by adding a number of checks against parse errors/live coding.
    
    The fixer conflict can be seen by checking out any of the new test case files and running the following command:
    `phpcbf -ps ./src/Standards/Generic/Tests/ControlStructures/InlineControlStructureUnitTest.3.inc --standard=squiz -vv`
    
    At the start of the fixer loop you can see that the sniff adds `{;}` which then causes other sniffs to kick in and conflict.
    Some of these other sniffs also still need fixes for this, but this PR addresses the part which is in the `Generic.ControlStructures.InlineControlStructure` sniff.
    
    Includes unit tests in dedicated unit test files to prevent these tests interfering with each other and/or the main test file.

