commit 2e7b3ae2362e87fcdc6df146ffbdaec926815acd
Author: jrfnl <jrfnl@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Nov 27 04:10:01 2018 +0100

    Squiz/LowercasePHPFunctions: add fixed file and various improvements
    
    The sniff contain a fixer, but didn't have a `fixed` file.
    
    While I was at it, I've reviewed the sniff and applied any improvements I could think of:
    * The sniff will now bow out early when the `T_STRING` content does not match a PHP native function.
    * The sniff did not detect non-lowercase PHP native functions when these were being imported via a `use function` statement.
        Detection of this has been added with a distinct, separate error code.
    * The sniff would incorrectly not throw an error when the namespace separator was used to indicate global namespace, i.e. `$a = \str_repeat();`
    * The sniff did not take randomly interspersed comments or PHPCS annotations into account.
    * Minor code de-duplication fixes.
    * More tests to document that some other `T_STRING`s, such as class and namespace declarations are not incorrectly recognized as function calls. This is mostly to guard against breaking this in the future.
    
    Includes additional unit tests for all fixes.

