commit ca1a806b72f910388afcec42bb47b2adb0ae37c7
Author: jrfnl <jrfnl@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon May 28 05:26:37 2018 +0200

    Squiz/OperatorSpacing: fix fixer conflict
    
    [Fixer conflicts series PR]
    
    Fixer conflict can be reproduced by running the below command against `master`:
    `phpcbf -p -s ./src/Standards/Squiz/Tests/Arrays/ArrayDeclarationUnitTest.1.inc --standard=Squiz`
    
    When there is a comment after an operator, the `Squiz.Commenting.PostStatementComment` sniff and the `Squiz.WhiteSpace.OperatorSpacing` sniffs would conflict, with the `PostStatementComment` sniff demanding a new line and the `OperatorSpacing` sniff demanding exactly one space.
    
    Along the same lines, if the next content is a PHPCS annotation on the next line, moving the annotation to be on the same line as the operator could change its meaning.
    
    I've chosen to fix this by throwing the error, but blocking auto-fixing when the next thing after the operator is a comment/annotation and the whitespace found is a new line.
    
    Includes unit test.

commit 8c1fa94d9da9becef53bb2dd9f7558fa6e6d099e
Author: jrfnl <jrfnl@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon May 28 00:39:39 2018 +0200

    Squiz/FunctionSpacing: fix fixer conflict - ignore function at start of embedded PHP
    
    [Fixer conflicts series PR]
    
    Fixer conflict can be reproduced by running the below command against master:
    phpcbf -p -s ./src/Standards/Generic/Tests/Files/LineEndingsUnitTest.inc --standard=Squiz
    
    Basically, the `Squiz.WhiteSpace.FunctionSpacing` sniff demands 2 blank lines between functions, while the `Squiz.PHP.EmbeddedPHP` sniff demands no blank lines at the start of an embedded PHP block, which causes a fixer conflict if a function is declared at the top of an embedded PHP block.
    
    To fix this, I've given precedence to the `EmbeddedPHP` sniff - i.e. no blank lines between the PHP open tag and the start of the function declaration. The `FunctionSpacing` will now ignore functions at the start of an embedded PHP block.
    
    Includes unit test.

commit b8085ac3950d9a0e224c761ab36116ba4cda0564
Author: photodude <walt@waltsorensen.com>
Date:   Sat May 26 22:53:47 2018 -0600

    getTestFiles() is not neded now
    
    If the getTestFiles() method is not there, PHPCS will automatically test all files which start with SniffNameUnitTest.... (.inc|js|css), so if there is no logic needed to determine which files to test - i.e. what we're left with now -, the whole method can be removed.

