commit d677d7018bdd152edfb51136465763002185be66
Author: Thiemo Kreuz <thiemowmde@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed Mar 21 14:08:35 2018 +0100

    Avoid calling File::hasCondition() twice
    
    This does not have a measurable effect on runtime, but immensely reduces the number of calls to this function. In the run I profiled hasCondition() was called about 18,000 times before and 10,000 times after this patch. The total runtime for these calls went from 1.3% to 1.1%.
    
    Note there are a few more sniffs where the exact same optimization can be applied.

commit b9fcde5b9b4f438afab44f262796a3621101d1ca
Author: Thiemo Kreuz <thiemowmde@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed Mar 21 14:02:39 2018 +0100

    Your code style is awkward

commit 046632b9b9f98a1b014bf22a996cca2a2bcccf29
Author: Thiemo Kreuz <thiemowmde@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Wed Mar 21 13:51:21 2018 +0100

    Avoid calling Config::__get() in a loop
    
    I was surprised to see the impact this minor optimization does have. In the example run I profiled Config::__get() was called about 88,000 times, and these calls accounted for about 4.6% of the total runtime.
    
    With this optimization applied Config::__get() is now called 5,000 times, and these calls now account for 0.3% of the total runtime.
    
    Yes, I'm talking total runtime. This means a run of 20 seconds total will be about a second faster.

