commit 15202d6d044de4ddd0bc72edb21aa8bebc630ee3
Author: jrfnl <jrfnl@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Sun Mar 11 00:53:52 2018 +0100

    Squiz/ControlSignature: improve handling of do/while structures
    
    Up to now, `do/while` structures would be examined based on the `do` token, while all other multi-keyword control structures were examined based on the keyword *after* the closing brace.
    
    As the fix in the previous commit depends on `$stackPtr` pointing to the keyword *after* the closing brace, the handling of `do/while` structures has been made consistent with how the other multi-keyword structures are handled.

commit 7ea5e9f2bbfa710b3fa869844981db0d82036b32
Author: jrfnl <jrfnl@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Sun Mar 11 00:49:06 2018 +0100

    Squiz/ControlSignature: bug fix no error being thrown icw trailing comment
    
    If there was a trailing comment after the closing brace of the preceding part a multi-keyword control structure, no errors would be thrown.
    
    While these are not auto-fixable, they should be reported and will be now.
    
    This also improves the compatibility of the sniff with the new PHPCS annotations.

