commit dad7574aa7c40ce4924f41a321edcfcb5bb1e96d
Author: jrfnl <jrfnl@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon Jan 15 00:44:16 2018 +0100

    Squiz/CommentedOutCode: correctly recognize multi-line `//` interspersed with PHPCS annotations
    
    Multi-line `//` comments with PHPCS annotations on their own line would be seen as several individual comments instead of being handled as one commented out code block.
    
    This commit now returns the last token which was recognized to be part of a comment block, to skip re-examining them.
    
    Includes additional unit test demonstrating the issue.

commit d120bb2e35dbaedd20d2f63ce946d5f75fc289b4
Author: jrfnl <jrfnl@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon Jan 15 00:40:54 2018 +0100

    Squiz/CommentedOutCode: improve handling of PHPCS annotations in comment blocks
    
    Only strip out the comment start delimiters for the comment type being handled.
    
    This way, the PHPCS annotations will be tokenized as their own token on re-tokenization and can be ignored more easily.

