commit 4795832bdac4ea18e7f6002f052ce5072f6bb1ad
Author: Greg Sherwood <gsherwood@squiz.net>
Date:   Tue Jul 19 15:25:30 2016 +1000

    Stopped gzipping files in the phar and just stripping whitespace instead.
    
    The use of gzip compression was stopping forking working when run from inside the phar. The only solution I could find was to add a sleep right after a fork, which seemed to allow something to catch up and not end up with a corrupt phar (syntax errors where everywhere). The current phars are 500k compressed, 1.8M uncompressed. Stripping whitespace by itself makes them 960k, which will have to do.

