commit 80b156de8d440b6245e6b1dd7f8df777d99064fa
Author: Greg Sherwood <gsherwood@squiz.net>
Date:   Wed Jan 27 11:47:19 2016 +1100

    Improved detection of STDIN being used.
    
    When using a command like "git diff --name-only | xargs phpcs", files are passed to PHPCS but STDIN is still reported as being available by stream_select(), so the files were ignored. Now, we just read STDIN properly (but non-blocking) and store that cotents for later use. If no files are available, and STDIN is empty, PHPCS will still wait for input on STDIN as it does already.

