commit bc8c394b381bc407df8feb8c83e500f75cb4d6a5
Author: Greg Sherwood <gsherwood@squiz.net>
Date:   Mon Mar 25 14:49:04 2013 +1100

    Improved support for including rulesets inside other rulesets using relative paths
    
    This is done by using the directory of a ruleset while processing it, rather than using the directory of the main standard. So if the main standard exists in location X and includes another standard in location Y, PHPCS is no longer trying to expand sniff codes by only looking in location X.

