commit 3aa8b4da1afa2395ac61404cfa38bdba10be9988
Author: Greg Sherwood <gsherwood@squiz.net>
Date:   Wed Nov 14 16:03:36 2012 +1100

    First pass at saving reports to a file instead of keeping everything in memory.
    Reports output content for a single file, which is stored into a temp file. The PHP_CodeSniffer_File object is then unset, freeing memory. At the end, the cached content is retrieved and the report adds the header and footer (if required). All reports are converted except for notifysend. Everything is very very rough. Still need to write the report cache directly to the output file if one is specified as there is no need for a temp file in this case.

