commit 3f1f0d943b9bf4d598ef0f9c491e3cdaff25a4d1
Author: Dorian Villet <dorian.villet@liip.ch>
Date:   Tue Oct 16 19:12:21 2012 +0300

    Fixes "Method name Foo::__soapCall is invalid."
    
    If the developer create a class extending the PHP native class \Soap_Client and override the __soapCall() method, PHPCS throws an error because "only magic methods should be prefixed with a double underscore".
    __soapCall() isn't a magic method, but it's named with two underscore, and as it is a PHP native method, I think it should be allowed by PHPCS.

