commit 2e0a57276f0b1956f9ef60cf3ecfee9c9781bcd0
Author: Greg Sherwood <gsherwood@squiz.net>
Date:   Mon Nov 17 05:59:24 2008 +0000

    Generic MultipleStatementAlignmentSniff now has a protected member var that allows it to ignore multi-line assignments. The PEAR standard makes use of this and adds a new sniff, MultiLineAssignmentSniff, to ensure multi-line assignments are indented correctly. The Squiz standard uses the PEAR standard for all statement alignment now, but turns all warnings into errors.
    
    
