commit cf135c2f4b240806e7c781557ecd492778035986
Author: Greg Sherwood <gsherwood@squiz.net>
Date:   Mon Nov 26 01:00:40 2007 +0000

    Added a new (often requested) feature to support tab indents. Using the new --tab-width command line arg, you can now tell PHP_CodeSniffer how many spaces each tab represents. PHP_CodeSniffer will replace your tabs with between 1 and  spaces so that all existing sniffs work correctly. The default value of zero stops PHP_CodeSniffer doing any replacements, so you can still write custom sniffs tha check for tabs. You can also save this setting using the config var tab_width.
    
    
    git-svn-id: http://svn.php.net/repository/pear/packages/PHP_CodeSniffer/trunk@247037 c90b9560-bf6c-de11-be94-00142212c4b1

